    • getContent

      public @NonNull List<Serializable> getContent()
      Gets the value of the content property.

      This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the content property.

      For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

          getContent().add(newItem);

      Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list JAXBElement<StrucDocSup > JAXBElement<StrucDocFootnoteRef> JAXBElement<StrucDocContent> JAXBElement<StrucDocRenderMultiMedia> JAXBElement<StrucDocFootnote> String JAXBElement<StrucDocLinkHtml> JAXBElement<StrucDocBr> JAXBElement <StrucDocSub>
